# Test-Driven Development Skill

## Purpose
Guide an AI agent through Test-Driven Development as defined by its creators: Kent Beck (TDD By Example, Test Desiderata) and Robert C. Martin (Three Laws of TDD). This skill includes foundational test quality properties and the TDD discipline of writing tests before code.

## Sections to Generate

### When to Use This Skill
Describe scenarios: implementing new features, fixing bugs, refactoring existing code, designing APIs through usage, exploring unfamiliar domains, any development where the design should emerge from tests.

